retroarch-configs changelog

2026-04-05  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v1.3

	* Remove redundant rewind_enable = false from all 9 .cfg files;
	  value identical to global retroarch.cfg — follows convention
	  established in retroarch-appletv4k v2.20 (preemptive_frames_enable
	  removal) and the stated README policy that overrides contain only
	  keys differing from global
	* Remove redundant run_ahead_frames = 1 from all 6 Tier 1 .cfg
	  files; value identical to global — Tier 1 cores inherit runahead
	  from global config
	* Mupen64Plus-Next header comment: note rewind constraint (#18300)
	  is satisfied by global rewind_enable = false
	* FinalBurn Neo header comment: note rewind constraint (#16374)
	  is satisfied by global rewind_enable = false
	* README.md: Update .cfg key counts in Supported Cores table;
	  remove rewind_enable row from Frontend Override Keys table;
	  update run_ahead_frames values from 0,1 to 0; bump version
	  1.2 → 1.3

2026-04-05  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v1.2

	* Fix Mupen64Plus-Next run_ahead_frames: 1 → 0; value contradicted
	  its own comment ("Re-enable run_ahead_frames per-game for light
	  titles") and was inconsistent with other Tier 2 cores (PCSX-ReARMed,
	  melonDS DS) which correctly used 0; fixes README per-game override
	  example (Super Mario 64) which was previously a no-op
	* Add video_frame_delay_auto = false to PCSX-ReARMed for consistency
	  with Mupen64Plus-Next and melonDS DS; all three Tier 2
	  interpreter-bound cores now uniformly disable auto frame delay
	* README.md: bump version 1.1 → 1.2; update PCSX-ReARMed .cfg key
	  count 7 → 8; add run-ahead note to Mupen64Plus-Next table row

2026-04-05  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v1.1

	* Add per-core CRT shader assignments to all .cfg files
	* Tier 1 cores: crt-easymode.slangp (scanline-only, low GPU
	  cost, compatible with global video_scale_integer = true)
	* Tier 2 cores (N64, PS1): zfast_crt.slangp (minimal GPU cost
	  for interpreter-bound cores)
	* melonDS DS: video_shader_enable = false (CRT shaders
	  unsuitable for NDS pixel art at 256×192; overrides global
	  video_shader_enable = true)
	* Add audio_resampler_quality = 2 to all Tier 2 cores
	  (Mupen64Plus-Next, PCSX-ReARMed, melonDS DS); fulfills
	  global retroarch.cfg comment "Per-core Lower (2) for Tier 2-3"
	* Cross-checked all per-core overrides against global
	  retroarch.cfg; no conflicts found; all global comments
	  promising per-core overrides now fulfilled
	* Audited global retroarch.cfg: no duplicate keys, no
	  contradictions, no removable keys, security keys present
	* README.md: Add CRT Shaders section with tier-to-shader
	  mapping; add shader column to Supported Cores table; add
	  audio_resampler_quality, video_shader, video_shader_enable
	  to Frontend Override Keys table; bump version 1.0 → 1.1

2026-04-04  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v1.0

	* Initial release: 9 per-core override sets for Apple TV 4K
	* Split previously commented core options from .cfg files into
	  separate .opt files; RetroArch loads core options only from
	  .opt files — commented values in .cfg were never applied
	* Tier 1 (Flawless) cores: Beetle PCE Fast, FinalBurn Neo,
	  Genesis Plus GX, Mesen, mGBA, Snes9x — all run runahead=1
	* Tier 2 (Good) cores: Mupen64Plus-Next, PCSX-ReARMed,
	  melonDS DS — no JIT on tvOS; runahead disabled or tuned
	* config/Beetle PCE Fast: 2 frontend keys, 2 core options
	  (CD image cache, sprite limit removal)
	* config/FinalBurn Neo: 2 frontend keys, no .opt file
	  (defaults sufficient; rewind conflicts with runahead #16374)
	* config/Genesis Plus GX: 2 frontend keys, 5 core options
	  (Nuked YM2612, low-pass filter, sprite limit, per-game BRAM)
	* config/Mesen: 3 frontend keys, 4 core options
	  (sprite limit, medium overclock, DMC pop reduction);
	  integer overscale=1 for 224p at 4K
	* config/mGBA: 2 frontend keys, 3 core options
	  (GBA color correction, smart interframe blending, low-pass)
	* config/Snes9x: 3 frontend keys, 2 core options
	  (sprite flicker reduction, light overclock);
	  integer overscale=1 for 224p at 4K
	* config/Mupen64Plus-Next: 6 frontend keys, 11 core options
	  (cached_interpreter, HLE RSP, GLideN64, frame duping,
	  threaded renderer, async color copy, no LOD emulation);
	  video_threaded=true, audio_latency=64
	* config/PCSX-ReARMed: 5 frontend keys, 7 core options
	  (DRC disabled, frame duping, auto frameskip at 33%,
	  synchronous GPU threading, async CD, PSX clock=57);
	  run_ahead_frames=0, video_threaded=true, audio_latency=48
	* config/melonDS DS: 6 frontend keys, 4 core options
	  (threaded renderer, JIT disabled, direct boot, top screen);
	  key prefix verified as melonds_ from JesseTG/melonds-ds
	  constants.hpp (not melondsds_); run_ahead_frames=0,
	  video_threaded=true, audio_latency=48
	* All .cfg files contain only RetroArch frontend keys
	* All .opt files contain only core-prefixed option keys
	* Cross-checked: every original commented core option
	  accounted for in corresponding .opt file
	* README.md: Supported cores table, file structure, override
	  key reference, installation, per-game override examples,
	  core option key verification sources
